In article <1993Oct1.095319.14168@umibox.hanse.de> root@umibox.hanse.de (Bernd Meyer) writes:
>Most of these rules make your system less secure, as they reduce the number
>of legal passwords, thus making it easier for Crack to get them.

They reduce the number of legal passwords, but that's irrelevant.
It's too expensive to run Crack over all legal passwords, even after
this number is reduced by an order of magnitude or so.  More
commonly, people run password attacks using dictionaries plus modification
rules.

